      "dimensions": 1,
      "description": "method -  - Describes where points are located.\n\n surface - Points are evenly distributed along the entire surface of the geometry. That is, smaller polygons receives fewer points on average than larger polygons, etc. perprim - Points are distributed equally amongst each primitive. That is, each polygon receives the same number of points. boundingbox - Points are distributed within the bounding box volume of the geometry. This can be faster, though less accurate than the volume method. approxvol - Points are evenly distributed within an approximation of the volume. Areas close to the surface may receive fewer points. volume - Points are evenly distributed within the entire volume of the geometry.",
